      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T06:41:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is possible that gRPC methods are called in parallel, so please protect mutable fields with a mutex.\n\nMy personal recommendation is to categorize fields in mutability. For example:\n\n srv *grpc.Server\n addr net.Addr\n psClient rtd.ProgressSinkClient\n testsToRequests map[string]string\n\n mu sync.Mutex\n reportedRequests map[string]struct{}",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 27,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 80
      },
      "revId": "ac054304a5697df10faa91a555d8cfac96b42dd5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "aad00bf4_ae670a4c",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast_rtd/internal/rpc/reports.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T06:41:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Please use pointer receiver for all methods of this type. Otherwise every method call requires copying the whole reportsServer struct.\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/wiki/CodeReviewComments#receiver-type",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ac054304a5697df10faa91a555d8cfac96b42dd5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
